column72: feedback. Here, you can give open feedback regarding concerns, improvement proposals and other thoughts.
Went a little fast at crosswalk by busses
The vehicle did not slow sufficiently when there were pedestrians in its path.
I believe that the system needs more light to work properly. Since the situation happens at the end of the day, the perception of the system to identify a person was all over the place.
i would like to see speed, turn signals and mirrors.

This was a different drive, I feel like the automated system was having a hard time keeping track of people and was visually seeing things that were not humans. It also made some weird decisions at one of the lights where there were multiple busses. Felt very unsafe during that situation.
Everything went fine, but I was nervous about the unsure pedestrian assessments.
It seems to have missed the construction barriers, also towards the end, it thought the lights in the distance were signs.
Interesting study again, As for the visuals, I do like them , seeing the pedestrian signs above people its cool, can be a lot at times but overall I enjoy it. Very unique way of seeing the world.
If these automated vehicles were to be driven around a shopping district or mall, would it be able to detect shopping carts or other moving vehicles like construction ones?
The pedestrian tagging was fairly poor in this shown video, as well as several yellow tags blending together making it difficult to differentiate these objects (as a human)
at night the sign detection was very messy, a lot of lights got recognized as light.
The car could not pick up on a large portion of lights, people, people walking intentions, or even bicycles and cars.

I stated this morning that I had a few issues with the automated driver coming to close to the curb, driving in a bicycle lane and almost hitting another car.  This evening I did notice that I THINK the car didn't stop at a stop sign,  But I could be wrong.  Something else puzzled me about the "people"  a few times, this morning and this evening it detected "people" in the sky.  What is that about?

The vehicle seemed to be really struggling to identify people in this video. There was a lot of excess flashing of people signs to the point of distraction and it being almost headache inducing. It made the whole video very unpleasant to watch. It did seem to identify cars and signs well and while it was identifying more things as potential people. it didn't seem to behave in an unusual manner in terms of driving.
